# Decide the Session-Start Briefing Contract

## Question

What does every agent wake up knowing? The rhizomatic briefing (claude
SessionStart hook) currently carries shallow session metadata. Decide: how
many observations and at what grain (today's index + N most-relevant atoms?
scoped to the session's repo/cwd?), ranking (recency vs relevance vs
graph-adjacency), staleness rule (durable decision pages outrank stale
observations — the temporal-gradient conflict rule, validated day one),
token budget per briefing, sensitive handling (include locally?), and WHICH
surfaces get it: claude hook, pi APPEND/extension, codex AGENTS — same
content everywhere or per-runtime shaping?

## Charter input (Joel, 2026-07-13): vision, inertia, and the annoyance bar

Joel: memory relates to VISION.md as "the vision an inertia of my systems" —
and the failure mode is a coding session "reminding me about some past
bullshit i don't care about." Principles for the grilling:

1. **Collision-triggered over ambient**: memory speaks when the session is
   about to CONTRADICT it, not when it merely remembers. Decisions already
   carry exit clauses (see files-are-truth: "named exit triggers", "do not
   relitigate") — recall surfaces a decision only when work approaches its
   territory, as guardrail not narration.
2. **Compile, don't converse**: vision belongs in machinery (validators,
   gates, charters) wherever possible; the briefing carries only what can't
   be compiled — current heading (active arc, frontier), ~3 lines, scoped
   to the session's repo/brief. Direction, not history.
3. **The annoyance bar is measurable**: a briefing line earns its place only
   if it changes what the session does. Consumption telemetry (fog) becomes
   interest decay — unengaged recall stops surfacing. Bar: not "worth
   recalling" but "worth interrupting with." Silence is the default state.
4. Vision docs sit at the TOP of the temporal gradient (canon); the
   reflector's monthly promotion feeds them; they outrank everything in
   recall conflicts.
